3. So g(y) = (f(x₀ + y) + f(x₀ - y)) / (2·f(x₀))
4. Using triangle inequality: |f(x₀ + y) + f(x₀ - y)| ≤ |f(x₀ + y)| + |f(x₀ - y)| ≤ 2
5. Therefore |g(y)| ≤ 2 / (2·|f(x₀)|) = 1/|f(x₀)|

But we need |g(y)| ≤ 1, which requires |f(x₀)| ≥ 1. Combined with |f(x₀)| ≤ 1, we need |f(x₀)| = 1.

